text: "You Ain't Woman Enough (To Take My Man)" is a 1966 song by country singer Loretta Lynn and is the title track to her seventh studio album You Ain't Woman Enough. It has been regarded as Lynn's signature songs. It has been covered by The Grateful Dead, Tina Turner, Martina McBride for her eighth studio album Timeless and Tanya Tucker re-recorded as a duet with Loretta Lynn for Lynn's 46th and final studio album Still Woman Enough. == Track listings == ;7" vinyl single * "You Ain't Woman Enough (To Take My Man)" – 2:11 * "God Gave Me a Heart to Forgive" – 2:54 ==References== Category:1966 songs Category:Country songs Category:Loretta Lynn songs Category:The Grateful Dead songs Category:Tina Turner songs Category:Martina McBride songs Category:Tanya Tucker songs Category:Paramore songs
